          SKOL Trademark

        

        
          Trademark Overview

          
          On Wednesday, May 18, 2016, a trademark application was filed for SKOL with the United States Patent and Trademark Office. The USPTO has given the SKOL trademark a serial number of 87041693. The federal status of this trademark filing is REGISTERED as of Tuesday, February 4, 2020.             Goods and ServicesTelevision broadcasting services; television transmission services; cable television broadcasting; radio broadcasting; Internet broadcasting; broadcasting programming on the Internet; information transmission via electronic communications networks; transmission of information through video communications systems; communications services, namely, audio and video broadcasting; broadcasting services and provision of telecommunication access to video and audio content provided via a video on demand service; streaming of audio material on the Internet; streaming of video material and podcasts on the Internet; wireless communications services, namely, transmission of text, graphics, data and entertainment information to mobile phones; mobile media services and entertainment services in the nature of electronic transmission of entertainment media content; in-stadium broadcasting services, namely, broadcasting video and audio content via electronic means within a stadium facility; webcasting services in the nature of providing on-line chat rooms and on-line interactive chat rooms with guests for transmission of messages among computer users concerning the fields of athletics and athletic competitions; providing multiple-user access to interactive computer databases in the fields of athletics and athletic competitions; transmission of information, sound, images and data by electronic communications networks, optical telecommunication networks, by satellite, by broadband, by cable and over the Internet; Providing facilities for broadcasting radio, television, video-on-demand and podcast and Internet broadcast studio facilities in connection with arena and stadium events; providing facilities for broadcasting audio and video programming over the Internet in connection with arena and stadium events
